	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				What people forget, and what we are talking about is a Newbie quest.<BR>
<BR>
You know, the ones where you turn in your black wolf pelt, or your bone chips, or your rat ears or whatever. The quests that start with one of your trainers. The quests that can be found in every Int/wizard casters guild in almost every city in Norrath.<BR>
<BR>
Felwite has a quest (black wolf pelt)<BR>
Erudin has a quest  (icy beads or so)<BR>
Quenos has ALOT of quests<BR>
Freeport (don't know, kos in caster guild, but i thought it was some orc pawn thing)<BR>
Ak'anom has a quest (forgot which one, probably some sprocket)<BR>
<BR>
All these quests give items that a Wizard can Use.<BR>
<BR>
All, but Neriak.<BR>
<BR>
That is the problem, and that is what is asked for, Not some lame excuse to port to another city where you are KoS as Dark Elf or to do a quest that is for level 30+ while you are still level 5.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

